<header>
	<img class="rightFloat" src="../media/WB_WTG01.jpg" mode="16" id="1004"  />Read the writing task from the previous exercise again and answer the questions. In most cases, there is more than one correct answer.


</header>
	
<section id="body">
	<img class="rightFloat" src="../media/WB_GW_003.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"  />
	
	<ol id="questionList">
	
	<li>Which of the following openings are the most appropriate for this letter?
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><g id="t1">I am writing to apply for the position of part-time bookshop assistant as advertised in The Post on Monday, 12th December.</g></li>
	<li><g id="t2">I'm writing about your ad for a shop assistant.</g></li>
	<li><g id="t3">I read with interest your advertisement in The Post on Monday, 12th December and I would like to apply for the position of part-time bookshop assistant.</g></li>
	<li><g id="t4">I saw your job in the paper and I want to apply.</g></li>
	<li><g id="t5">I've always wanted a job in a shop so when I saw your advert in the paper on Monday, I decided to apply.</g></li>
	<li><g id="t6">I would like to express my interest in the position of part-time bookshop assistant as advertised in The Post on Monday, 12th December.</g></li>
	</list></li>
	<p class="linespace"></p>
	<li>Which is the best way to refer to your CV?
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><g id="t7">Read my CV for more details.</g></li>
	<li><g id="t8">You can check all this by looking at my CV.</g></li>
	<li><g id="t9">have a look at my CV and you'll see that ...</g></li>
	<li><g id="t10">As you can see from my CV, ...</g></li>
	<li><g id="t11">Please find enclosed my CV.</g></li>
	<li><g id="t12">Anyway, it's all in my CV so you can see for yourself.</g></li>
	</list></li>
	<p class="linespace"></p>
	<li>Which is the best way to refer to your experience?
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><g id="t13">I've worked in loads of bookshops before.</g></li>
	<li><g id="t14">I have three years' experience in the retail industry.</g></li>
	<li><g id="t15">I have simply years of experience.</g></li>
	<li><g id="t16">I've got lots of experience in this business already.</g></li>
	<li><g id="t17">You'll be amazed at how experienced I am!</g></li>
	<li><g id="t18">I have considerable experience in sales.</g></li>
	</list></li>
	<p class="linespace"></p>
	<li>Which is the best way to express your availability for interview?
	<list class="answerList">
	<li><g id="t19">I'm free all the time.</g></li>
	<li><g id="t20">I can come for an interview at a moment's notice.</g></li>
	<li><g id="t21">I can make it to an interview any time.</g></li>
	<li><g id="t22">Any time that suits you is fine by me.</g></li>
	<li><g id="t23">I am available for an interview at your convenience.</g></li>
	<li><g id="t24">I can have an interview whenever you like.</g></li>
	</list></li>
	<p class="linespace"></p>
	</ol>
